President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Beth Robinson for Under Secretary of the Department of Energy, Jessica Garfola Wright for Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness, Nisha Desai Biswal for Assistant Secretary for South Asian Affairs at the Department of State, Julia Frifield for Assistant Secretary for Legislative Affairs at the Department of State, Frank A. Rose for Assistant Secretary for Verification and Compliance at the Department of State, Scott S. Dahl for Inspector General at the Department of Labor, Tim Broas for Ambassador to the Kingdom of the Netherlands at the Department of State, and Adam M. Scheinman for Special Representative of the President for Nuclear Nonproliferation at the Department of State. President Obama expressed confidence in the abilities of these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the future.